In article <1993Aug26.190740.4546@cybernet.cse.fau.edu> michaelb@cse.fau.edu (Michael Rogero Brown) writes:

> I`ve always wondered if such a document existed which did the same in
> regards to e-mail discussion groups.  (not just regular person-person email)

> I know some lists exist for specific groups, but was wondering if
> there existed a more generic version.

I would recommend 'Putting out the Flames: The Etiquette and Law of
E-mail' by Joanne Goode and Maggie Johnson (ONLINE, November, 1991,
pg. 61-65). While this article pertains mostly to person-person mail,
there are some very general applicable guidelines on pg. 62. (Note:
this article does not necessarily pertain to Usenet, but the section
under Survival Skills is definitely applicable.)

-laurie
